  "text": "The presence of PCPE-1 in corneal stroma, which has a fibrillar collagen ECM, is consistent with its previously demonstrated role in fibrillar collagen biosynthesis [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Indeed, we found WT keratocytes to produce readily detectable PCPE-1 and found keratocytes isolated from Pcolce −/− corneas to display a decrease in the extent of procollagen I processing. However, this difference in procollagen processing did not correspond to readily discernable differences in corneal opacity or collagen content following keratectomy, nor with a readily discernable [CITATION_4] ). Since we do not know the extent to which each of these factors affects the Fig. 7 Distributions of PCPE-1 in injured mouse cornea.",
